# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: UnionKingdom | Scene: UnionLoop
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah poured over the documents until late at night."
    new "Sarah poured over the documents until late at night."

    old "She formulated her strategy on approaching the others and securing their votes."
    new "She formulated her strategy on approaching the others and securing their votes."

    old "She had to make her next moves carefully, but equally knew she could not lean back and wait things out."
    new "She had to make her next moves carefully, but equally knew she could not lean back and wait things out."

    old "Now she would act."
    new "Now she would act."

    old "Sarah had scheduled her meeting with Queen Maeiv."
    new "Sarah had scheduled her meeting with Queen Maeiv."

    old "Though she had met with Maeiv a few times now, she had in truth not truly gotten to know her."
    new "Though she had met with Maeiv a few times now, she had in truth not truly gotten to know her."

    old "Most of what she knew came from the books she had read."
    new "Most of what she knew came from the books she had read."

    old "Most all warned that she was not someone to underestimate."
    new "Most all warned that she was not someone to underestimate."

    old "Sarah knocked on the door to Queen Maeiv's room."
    new "Sarah knocked on the door to Queen Maeiv's room."

    old "Enter."
    new "Enter."

    old "Her voice was calm, yet forceful."
    new "Her voice was calm, yet forceful."

    old "Entering the room like a servant called, Sarah did her best to straighten her back and look like a peer."
    new "Entering the room like a servant called, Sarah did her best to straighten her back and look like a peer."

    old "No, she thought to herself. You are her peer."
    new "No, she thought to herself. You are her peer."

    old "Still, seeing the woman sit so comfortably in her chair, she made the business of ruling seem so effortless."
    new "Still, seeing the woman sit so comfortably in her chair, she made the business of ruling seem so effortless."

    old "Queen Maeiv, I am glad we could meet."
    new "Queen Maeiv, I am glad we could meet."

    old "Of course, my dear, of course! Please, take a seat."
    new "Of course, my dear, of course! Please, take a seat."

    old "Sarah walked over and sat down."
    new "Sarah walked over and sat down."

    old "Queen Maeiv continued to read, not even looking up to acknowledge her."
    new "Queen Maeiv continued to read, not even looking up to acknowledge her."

    old "For a moment, the room was quiet."
    new "For a moment, the room was quiet."

    old "I'm very sorry, Sarah. I'm almost done with this, I promise. They badger me with this all day."
    new "I'm very sorry, Sarah. I'm almost done with this, I promise. They badger me with this all day."

    old "Ooh, I am well aware."
    new "Ooh, I am well aware."

    old "Back home it's the same for me. Never a moment of rest."
    new "Back home it's the same for me. Never a moment of rest."

    old "Queen Maeiv nodded as she continued to read."
    new "Queen Maeiv nodded as she continued to read."

    old "Yes, that must be a lot. But surely you have some good people about to help you, yes?"
    new "Yes, that must be a lot. But surely you have some good people about to help you, yes?"

    old "The members of my council have been loyal to my family for years. They're all very capable."
    new "The members of my council have been loyal to my family for years. They're all very capable."

    old "Queen Maeiv chuckled."
    new "Queen Maeiv chuckled."

    old "Wish I could say the same."
    new "Wish I could say the same."

    old "The nobles here are a barrel of snakes."
    new "The nobles here are a barrel of snakes."

    old "Every single one of them imagines that I won't last, and they all plot to sit in my chair one day."
    new "Every single one of them imagines that I won't last, and they all plot to sit in my chair one day."

    old "She looked up and put the document away."
    new "She looked up and put the document away."

    old "And yet, I remain, and they come and go."
    new "And yet, I remain, and they come and go."

    old "Good people are worth their weight in gold."
    new "Good people are worth their weight in gold."

    old "Maeiv smiled back."
    new "Maeiv smiled back."

    old "Quiet so."
    new "Quiet so."

    old "And your brother. Thomas was it?"
    new "And your brother. Thomas was it?"

    old "Still a cripple?"
    new "Still a cripple?"

    old "She could be as blunt as she could be diplomatic. Sarah winced at the comment, but fought to keep her composure."
    new "She could be as blunt as she could be diplomatic. Sarah winced at the comment, but fought to keep her composure."

    old "My brother is healthy."
    new "My brother is healthy."

    old "Ooh, was I wrongly informed? I heard he was a bit odd in the head ever since...well that whole mess the boy Marion caused."
    new "Ooh, was I wrongly informed? I heard he was a bit odd in the head ever since...well that whole mess the boy Marion caused."

    old "No. He simply does not have a heart for ruling."
    new "No. He simply does not have a heart for ruling."

    old "Maeiv's lips curled into a smile."
    new "Maeiv's lips curled into a smile."

    old "There wasn't much joy in it. More like a predator."
    new "There wasn't much joy in it. More like a predator."

    old "And you do?"
    new "And you do?"

    old "I do what I must. Taking on my family's duties is an honour."
    new "I do what I must. Taking on my family's duties is an honour."

    old "You're very strong to do so, Sarah. Very strong indeed."
    new "You're very strong to do so, Sarah. Very strong indeed."

    old "And the death of your brother. Thomas was it?"
    new "And the death of your brother. Thomas was it?"

    old "I pray that doesn't weigh too heavy on you."
    new "I pray that doesn't weigh too heavy on you."

    old "I have had my share of tragedies in life."
    new "I have had my share of tragedies in life."

    old "But I persevere."
    new "But I persevere."

    old "Now, I think you've come to discuss the matter of the military with me."
    new "Now, I think you've come to discuss the matter of the military with me."

    old "I assume you've read my proposal on unifying our armies, yes?"
    new "I assume you've read my proposal on unifying our armies, yes?"

    old "I did read it in fact."
    new "I did read it in fact."

    old "And? It makes perfect sense, yes?"
    new "And? It makes perfect sense, yes?"

    old "The Mythrans will land on our shore, unified. We must be the same."
    new "The Mythrans will land on our shore, unified. We must be the same."

    old "The military is the most crucial part of all of this."
    new "The military is the most crucial part of all of this."

    old "I agree, actually."
    new "I agree, actually."

    old "Uniting our armies should be paramount. Otherwise, they will take us down one-by-one."
    new "Uniting our armies should be paramount. Otherwise, they will take us down one-by-one."

    old "Quite so, my dear, quite so!"
    new "Quite so, my dear, quite so!"

    old "I knew you would be clever enough to see things my way."
    new "I knew you would be clever enough to see things my way."

    old "I hope that I can count on your vote for my proposal?"
    new "I hope that I can count on your vote for my proposal?"

    old "Sarah forced a smile. Her proposal, as she was in charge of the whole idea."
    new "Sarah forced a smile. Her proposal, as she was in charge of the whole idea."

    old "Of course, and I hope I can count on your vote as well."
    new "Of course, and I hope I can count on your vote as well."

    old "Ooh, you're a delight my dear, of course. My vote, your vote. So long as we agree, I am most content."
    new "Ooh, you're a delight my dear, of course. My vote, your vote. So long as we agree, I am most content."

    old "Then the matter is settled. We agree."
    new "Then the matter is settled. We agree."

    old "Quite so."
    new "Quite so."

    old "Sarah was happy to have Maeiv's support for her position."
    new "Sarah was happy to have Maeiv's support for her position."

    old "Returning to her room, she continued to prepare for the next meeting."
    new "Returning to her room, she continued to prepare for the next meeting."

    old "No, I don't agree, actually."
    new "No, I don't agree, actually."

    old "She saw a moment of surprise in Maeiv's face."
    new "She saw a moment of surprise in Maeiv's face."

    old "Ooh...I must admit, my dear, this has caught me somewhat by surprise."
    new "Ooh...I must admit, my dear, this has caught me somewhat by surprise."

    old "Because I took the Duke for a fool, not you."
    new "Because I took the Duke for a fool, not you."

    old "Sarah smiled, shrugging off the insult."
    new "Sarah smiled, shrugging off the insult."

    old "Rosanna has the largest army. We are the most battle-hardened. Tested by the Tribes and during the uprising."
    new "Rosanna has the largest army. We are the most battle-hardened. Tested by the Tribes and during the uprising."

    old "You say you are tested."
    new "You say you are tested."

    old "I say you have suffered two major conflicts and are in a poor condition for a third."
    new "I say you have suffered two major conflicts and are in a poor condition for a third."

    old "Sarah kept her face still, revealing no emotion."
    new "Sarah kept her face still, revealing no emotion."

    old "Describe it however you might."
    new "Describe it however you might."

    old "I don't think uniting our armies is a good idea."
    new "I don't think uniting our armies is a good idea."

    old "My soldiers will die for me and my country. They will fight for their families."
    new "My soldiers will die for me and my country. They will fight for their families."

    old "They won't do the same as part of a faceless army that holds no true allegiance to anyone other than an abstract Union."
    new "They won't do the same as part of a faceless army that holds no true allegiance to anyone other than an abstract Union."

    old "And when the Mythrans come?"
    new "And when the Mythrans come?"

    old "We can fight them together, but we shall each command our own army."
    new "We can fight them together, but we shall each command our own army."

    old "Maeiv sighed."
    new "Maeiv sighed."

    old "Do you think the Mythrans fight like that? Of course not."
    new "Do you think the Mythrans fight like that? Of course not."

    old "They unite under a single banner, because they understand that division is weakness in war."
    new "They unite under a single banner, because they understand that division is weakness in war."

    old "A fine argument, but I suspect your motives are not so pure."
    new "A fine argument, but I suspect your motives are not so pure."

    old "Ooh?"
    new "Ooh?"

    old "Normandi has a fine army, but it is small."
    new "Normandi has a fine army, but it is small."

    old "Of course you would wish to unite our banners, because yours alone is the smallest of all."
    new "Of course you would wish to unite our banners, because yours alone is the smallest of all."

    old "I thought among women, we wouldn't be measuring who has the biggest."
    new "I thought among women, we wouldn't be measuring who has the biggest."

    old "But I suppose it will always come down to that."
    new "But I suppose it will always come down to that."

    old "I would hope you could see reason and bring yourself to support my position."
    new "I would hope you could see reason and bring yourself to support my position."

    old "Maeiv frowned."
    new "Maeiv frowned."

    old "No, I don't think I will."
    new "No, I don't think I will."

    old "Edmond and Duke Antonio are less short-sighted than you. They will see reason and support me."
    new "Edmond and Duke Antonio are less short-sighted than you. They will see reason and support me."

    old "That will give me enough votes to secure what I wanted regardless."
    new "That will give me enough votes to secure what I wanted regardless."

    old "I cannot bring you to reconsider?"
    new "I cannot bring you to reconsider?"

    old "For a while, she was quiet as her eyes roamed across the room."
    new "For a while, she was quiet as her eyes roamed across the room."

    old "Well, let us never say never. I'd hate to start off this Council with a dispute."
    new "Well, let us never say never. I'd hate to start off this Council with a dispute."

    old "Perhaps, if you could bring yourself to bring balance in another way, this issue might prove less problematic."
    new "Perhaps, if you could bring yourself to bring balance in another way, this issue might prove less problematic."

    old "Another way?"
    new "Another way?"

    old "Normandi is famous for our craftsmen, but we are experts in the finer crafts. Gemcutting, jewelcrafting, painting."
    new "Normandi is famous for our craftsmen, but we are experts in the finer crafts. Gemcutting, jewelcrafting, painting."

    old "Not exactly industries of war."
    new "Not exactly industries of war."

    old "By contrast, the forges of your country run hot and constant with the battering of new swords and armors."
    new "By contrast, the forges of your country run hot and constant with the battering of new swords and armors."

    old "If you were willing to pledge the output of your nation's blacksmiths to my country, it would go a long way in supporting my army."
    new "If you were willing to pledge the output of your nation's blacksmiths to my country, it would go a long way in supporting my army."

    old "In such a case, though our armies would be seperate, we might still share a more balanced understanding."
    new "In such a case, though our armies would be seperate, we might still share a more balanced understanding."

    old "Sarah considered the proposal."
    new "Sarah considered the proposal."

    old "Offering it would gain her Maeiv's support in the vote to keep their armies apart."
    new "Offering it would gain her Maeiv's support in the vote to keep their armies apart."

    old "But instead, she would be empowering the army of her closest neighbour."
    new "But instead, she would be empowering the army of her closest neighbour."

    old "Yet if she failed to procure the needed votes, the others might agree to unite their armies."
    new "Yet if she failed to procure the needed votes, the others might agree to unite their armies."

    old "In such a situation, Rosanna would have to join, or otherwise be left as the smallest army on the continent. Either way, an unwelcome proposition."
    new "In such a situation, Rosanna would have to join, or otherwise be left as the smallest army on the continent. Either way, an unwelcome proposition."

    old "Agree, pledge your industry to Maeiv"
    new "Agree, pledge your industry to Maeiv"

    old "This we can do. I will pledge to use my nation's industry to equip your armies."
    new "This we can do. I will pledge to use my nation's industry to equip your armies."

    old "This will help each of us when the Mythrans attack."
    new "This will help each of us when the Mythrans attack."

    old "I am glad that we are able to come to an understanding. I knew you were no true fool."
    new "I am glad that we are able to come to an understanding. I knew you were no true fool."

    old "And your vote?"
    new "And your vote?"

    old "You have it."
    new "You have it."

    old "I will support your proposal in rejecting a unified army."
    new "I will support your proposal in rejecting a unified army."

    old "Sarah stood up and gave a quick curtsy."
    new "Sarah stood up and gave a quick curtsy."

    old "She had gotten what she came for."
    new "She had gotten what she came for."

    old "Sarah left the room."
    new "Sarah left the room."

    old "Refuse, you don't need her vote"
    new "Refuse, you don't need her vote"

    old "No. The resources and industry of my nation are my own. They will not go to support your armies."
    new "No. The resources and industry of my nation are my own. They will not go to support your armies."

    old "Queen Maeiv's face turned to a scowl."
    new "Queen Maeiv's face turned to a scowl."

    old "Very well, Sarah. Then you know my answer."
    new "Very well, Sarah. Then you know my answer."

    old "She stood up and left the room."
    new "She stood up and left the room."

    old "Sarah searched the castle, hoping to find Duke Antonio."
    new "Sarah searched the castle, hoping to find Duke Antonio."

    old "For much of her day, he was nowhere to be found."
    new "For much of her day, he was nowhere to be found."

    old "Finally, near the late night, Sarah managed to track him down."
    new "Finally, near the late night, Sarah managed to track him down."

    old "Surprisingly, she found him in the royal gardens."
    new "Surprisingly, she found him in the royal gardens."

    old "Duke Antonio!"
    new "Duke Antonio!"

    old "Sarah called out to him as she crossed the distance between them."
    new "Sarah called out to him as she crossed the distance between them."

    old "He turned to face her, a warm smile on his face."
    new "He turned to face her, a warm smile on his face."

    old "Aah, Sarah."
    new "Aah, Sarah."

    old "You attending a ball nearby?"
    new "You attending a ball nearby?"

    old "Sarah looked at him, confused."
    new "Sarah looked at him, confused."

    old "No, I was looking for you, actually."
    new "No, I was looking for you, actually."

    old "Ah, my mistake. You simply looked so lovely, I just assumed."
    new "Ah, my mistake. You simply looked so lovely, I just assumed."

    old "Sarah forced a smile."
    new "Sarah forced a smile."

    old "He was a flirt, that much had become clear during the feast, when he had taken in with the servant girl."
    new "He was a flirt, that much had become clear during the feast, when he had taken in with the servant girl."

    old "Thank you for your kind words, but I was hoping we could speak of more serious matters than dressed and balls."
    new "Thank you for your kind words, but I was hoping we could speak of more serious matters than dressed and balls."

    old "Duke Antonio sighed deeply."
    new "Duke Antonio sighed deeply."

    old "Aah, yes. That matter."
    new "Aah, yes. That matter."

    old "Council mattter."
    new "Council mattter."

    old "Do you have a moment to speak with me?"
    new "Do you have a moment to speak with me?"

    old "He frowned."
    new "He frowned."

    old "It was concerning...the military, was it?"
    new "It was concerning...the military, was it?"

    old "Exactly. Do you have a moment?"
    new "Exactly. Do you have a moment?"

    old "Duke Antonio gestured towards the gardens."
    new "Duke Antonio gestured towards the gardens."

    old "I was about to go for a late night walk, but you are welcome to join me."
    new "I was about to go for a late night walk, but you are welcome to join me."

    old "Sarah walked up closer, walking side-by-side with the Duke."
    new "Sarah walked up closer, walking side-by-side with the Duke."

    old "I must admit, I have been looking for you all day."
    new "I must admit, I have been looking for you all day."

    old "Duke Antonio smiled."
    new "Duke Antonio smiled."

    old "Aah, wish that I had known I was being pursued by one such as you. I might have actually bothered to been found."
    new "Aah, wish that I had known I was being pursued by one such as you. I might have actually bothered to been found."

    old "I simply did not suspect I would end up finding you here."
    new "I simply did not suspect I would end up finding you here."

    old "He raised on eyebrow."
    new "He raised on eyebrow."

    old "I didn't take you for one who appreciated gardens and flowers."
    new "I didn't take you for one who appreciated gardens and flowers."

    old "No, people tend not to think of me like that."
    new "No, people tend not to think of me like that."

    old "People see what they like to see. In me, they see a simple brute, who cares only for money."
    new "People see what they like to see. In me, they see a simple brute, who cares only for money."

    old "It makes the world simple, reducing everyone down to one or two things."
    new "It makes the world simple, reducing everyone down to one or two things."

    old "I am well aware, Duke Antonio. I should not have rushed to judgement."
    new "I am well aware, Duke Antonio. I should not have rushed to judgement."

    old "He waved his hands, as if the matter was of no import."
    new "He waved his hands, as if the matter was of no import."

    old "Forget it. You meant no insult by it."
    new "Forget it. You meant no insult by it."

    old "They continued to walk through the vast, almost endless, gardens of the palace."
    new "They continued to walk through the vast, almost endless, gardens of the palace."

    old "Each part was perfectly maintained."
    new "Each part was perfectly maintained."

    old "You should come visit Medini some day. We have some of the most beautiful gardens in all the Union."
    new "You should come visit Medini some day. We have some of the most beautiful gardens in all the Union."

    old "I would like that, but perhaps another time. This visit alone has been quite a burden."
    new "I would like that, but perhaps another time. This visit alone has been quite a burden."

    old "Still, I like to think that our nations have always had good relations."
    new "Still, I like to think that our nations have always had good relations."

    old "It was true. Rosanna and Medini, kept apart by the two nations that laid between them, had rarely ever seen direct conflict."
    new "It was true. Rosanna and Medini, kept apart by the two nations that laid between them, had rarely ever seen direct conflict."

    old "Distant neighbours made for good neighbours."
    new "Distant neighbours made for good neighbours."

    old "But enough of flowers and gardens. You said you wished to speak of serious matters."
    new "But enough of flowers and gardens. You said you wished to speak of serious matters."

    old "Well, go ahead."
    new "Well, go ahead."

    old "The proposal on the table is to unify our armies into one Union army."
    new "The proposal on the table is to unify our armies into one Union army."

    old "A well considered proposal by Queen Maeiv."
    new "A well considered proposal by Queen Maeiv."

    old "I happen to agree with her position."
    new "I happen to agree with her position."

    old "Do you now?"
    new "Do you now?"

    old "Have you given thought to the fact that she stands to gain the most out of that?"
    new "Have you given thought to the fact that she stands to gain the most out of that?"

    old "Her army is small. No doubt she wishes to bring them all under one banner."
    new "Her army is small. No doubt she wishes to bring them all under one banner."

    old "One banner that she will hope to fly in her name."
    new "One banner that she will hope to fly in her name."

    old "Well, it would be under all our names, of course."
    new "Well, it would be under all our names, of course."

    old "Perhaps, but the way things are officially and how they are in truth...these things can vary."
    new "Perhaps, but the way things are officially and how they are in truth...these things can vary."

    old "Still, we must consider the matter of military effectiveness."
    new "Still, we must consider the matter of military effectiveness."

    old "The Mythrans will not land on our shores alone."
    new "The Mythrans will not land on our shores alone."

    old "Duke Antonio nodded again."
    new "Duke Antonio nodded again."

    old "This too is true, but are you familiar with the history of my nation?"
    new "This too is true, but are you familiar with the history of my nation?"

    old "In what sense?"
    new "In what sense?"

    old "In how we fight our wars."
    new "In how we fight our wars."

    old "You...rely on mercenaries."
    new "You...rely on mercenaries."

    old "Quite so. When we have need of it, we spend our gold and draw on the old contracts that have served us for centuries."
    new "Quite so. When we have need of it, we spend our gold and draw on the old contracts that have served us for centuries."

    old "Your proposed Union army...I doubt it would accept mercenaries in its ranks."
    new "Your proposed Union army...I doubt it would accept mercenaries in its ranks."

    old "Of course not. A sellsword fights for money."
    new "Of course not. A sellsword fights for money."

    old "And so instead, what do you expect Medini to offer to this new Union army?"
    new "And so instead, what do you expect Medini to offer to this new Union army?"

    old "Let me answer my own question. You would ask us to send our sons and daughters. To sacrifice the young on the altar of war."
    new "Let me answer my own question. You would ask us to send our sons and daughters. To sacrifice the young on the altar of war."

    old "What a horror."
    new "What a horror."

    old "Sarah frowned. She had not considered this fact yet."
    new "Sarah frowned. She had not considered this fact yet."

    old "It was true that if they were to form a unified army, each nation would have to supply soldiers."
    new "It was true that if they were to form a unified army, each nation would have to supply soldiers."

    old "For all of them, this was little problem. For Medini, it meant drafting their citizens, something they had never done before."
    new "For all of them, this was little problem. For Medini, it meant drafting their citizens, something they had never done before."

    old "So you understand, I am hesitant to sign away the lives of our young for such a project."
    new "So you understand, I am hesitant to sign away the lives of our young for such a project."

    old "I understand. Though I wish you could see the wisdom in it."
    new "I understand. Though I wish you could see the wisdom in it."

    old "But I will admit, I am not unmoved by your arguments. And perhaps, unusual times require unusual sacrifice."
    new "But I will admit, I am not unmoved by your arguments. And perhaps, unusual times require unusual sacrifice."

    old "So you will support my position?"
    new "So you will support my position?"

    old "The Duke firmly shook his head."
    new "The Duke firmly shook his head."

    old "No, not as it is."
    new "No, not as it is."

    old "What then?"
    new "What then?"

    old "I will require convincing."
    new "I will require convincing."

    old "Convincing?"
    new "Convincing?"

    old "The Duke stopped and looked at her."
    new "The Duke stopped and looked at her."

    old "Sarah suddenly realized how alone they were, lost in the sea of endless bushes and plants."
    new "Sarah suddenly realized how alone they were, lost in the sea of endless bushes and plants."

    old "In Medini you are quite famous. They write songs of your incredible beauty."
    new "In Medini you are quite famous. They write songs of your incredible beauty."

    old "Allow me to see if the tales are true, and I will consider supporting your proposal."
    new "Allow me to see if the tales are true, and I will consider supporting your proposal."

    old "The slap rang out before he had barely gotten the words out."
    new "The slap rang out before he had barely gotten the words out."

    old "Sarah saw his stunned expression."
    new "Sarah saw his stunned expression."

    old "You are a sick pervert if these were your designs."
    new "You are a sick pervert if these were your designs."

    old "I am a married woman."
    new "I am a married woman."

    old "Perhaps in Medini, such vows mean little to a whoring fiend like you, but I spoke them with all my heart."
    new "Perhaps in Medini, such vows mean little to a whoring fiend like you, but I spoke them with all my heart."

    old "I didn't meant to-"
    new "I didn't meant to-"

    old "Sarah interrupted him."
    new "Sarah interrupted him."

    old "Enough from you. You have said more than plenty."
    new "Enough from you. You have said more than plenty."

    old "You struck me! You have no right-"
    new "You struck me! You have no right-"

    old "No right?!"
    new "No right?!"

    old "Yes, I have struck you, but only because you struck me first with your words!"
    new "Yes, I have struck you, but only because you struck me first with your words!"

    old "And consider it a mercy!"
    new "And consider it a mercy!"

    old "A mercy?"
    new "A mercy?"

    old "Yes, for if I were to write my husband of what you have done today, your life would be all but forfeit!"
    new "Yes, for if I were to write my husband of what you have done today, your life would be all but forfeit!"

    old "Yes, you know his name."
    new "Yes, you know his name."

    old "He is a great military leader, but equally skilled with a blade."
